---
// Hero — full-page bilingual reading column on the right,
// dual CTAs and waitlist signup on the left.
---

<section class="hero" id="top">
  <p class="eyebrow">
    <span data-i18n="hero.eyebrow"
      >Privacy-first · Bilingual · Open source · MIT</span
    >
  </p>
  <div class="hero-grid">
    <div>
      <h1 class="serif">
        <span data-i18n="hero.t1">Read the web in two languages</span><span
          data-i18n="hero.t1b">,</span
        >
        <em data-i18n="hero.t2">without losing</em><span data-i18n="hero.t3"
          > the original.</span
        >
      </h1>
      <p class="pitch">
        <strong data-i18n="hero.p1">Margin</strong>
        <span data-i18n="hero.p2"
          > inserts the translation beneath each paragraph. The original stays
          exactly where it was. Bring your own API key — OpenAI, Anthropic, or
          Google. No Margin server, no account, no telemetry.</span
        >
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a
          class="cta primary"
          href="https://github.com/linyiru/margin-read/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener">
          <span data-i18n="hero.cta1">Install from source</span>
          <span class="cta-meta mono" data-i18n="hero.cta1m"
            >unpacked · MV3</span
          >
        </a>
        <button class="cta" id="openWaitlistBtn" type="button">
          <span data-i18n="hero.cta2">Notify me on launch</span>
          <span class="cta-meta mono" data-i18n="hero.cta2m"
            >Chrome Web Store · soon</span
          >
        </button>
      </div>
      <form class="signup hidden" id="signup-form">
        <input
          type="email"
          placeholder="you@example.com"
          required
          data-i18n-attr="placeholder"
          data-i18n="hero.email_ph"
        />
        <button type="submit" data-i18n="hero.cta">Submit</button>
      </form>
      <p class="signup-note">
        <span class="dot">●</span>
        <span data-i18n="hero.note"
          >No spam. No third-party tracking. Two CTAs, equal weight: try it now,
          or wait for the store.</span
        >
      </p>
    </div>
    <div>
      <div class="hero-page" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="hp-corner mono">
          <span>FIG. 01</span><span>READING / PARALLEL</span>
        </div>
        <div class="hp-spine"></div>
        <div class="hp-meta mono" data-i18n="hero.hp_meta">
          arXiv · cs.CL · 2024 · 12 min read
        </div>
        <h4 class="hp-title serif" data-i18n="hero.hp_title">
          Mixture of Experts: A Survey for Long-Context Models
        </h4>
        <div class="hp-byline mono" data-i18n="hero.hp_byline">
          — J. Smolinski · Y. Tanaka · M. Reyes
        </div>
        <p class="hp-para hp-en" data-i18n="hero.hp_p1">
          Most translation extensions replace the page. Margin does the
          opposite — the original stays, and the translation grows beneath,
          paragraph by paragraph.
        </p>
        <p class="hp-para hp-zh" data-i18n="hero.hp_p1z">
          大多數翻譯外掛把整頁取代。Margin 反其道而行——原文留下，譯文一段一段在下方長出來。
        </p>
        <p class="hp-para hp-en" data-i18n="hero.hp_p2">
          When the original is one glance away, you verify a translated phrase
          the moment it feels off.
        </p>
        <p class="hp-para hp-zh" data-i18n="hero.hp_p2z">
          當原文只在一瞥之間，你能在感覺翻譯不對勁的瞬間立刻驗證。
        </p>
        <div class="hp-cap mono">
          <span>● TRANSLATED IN-PLACE</span><span data-i18n="hero.hp_cap2"
            >PARAGRAPH × PARAGRAPH</span
          >
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="marquee">
    <div class="marquee-track" id="marquee">
      <span><span class="star">✦</span> Privacy-first</span>
      <span><span class="star">✦</span> 隱私優先</span>
      <span><span class="star">✦</span> Bring Your Own Key</span>
      <span><span class="star">✦</span> 自帶 API Key</span>
      <span><span class="star">✦</span> No telemetry</span>
      <span><span class="star">✦</span> 不追蹤</span>
      <span><span class="star">✦</span> Open Source · MIT</span>
      <span><span class="star">✦</span> 開源 MIT</span>
      <span><span class="star">✦</span> Chrome MV3</span>
      <span><span class="star">✦</span> OpenAI · Claude · Gemini</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
